	url = {https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105036474354?origin=resultslist},
	abstract = {Short video advertising has become a critical channel for brand marketing, yet systematic analysis of user-generated emotional responses remains limited. This study examines 30,726 user comments on CHAGEE's short video advertisements collected from Douyin and Xiaohongshu platforms (August 2023 to January 2025) to investigate emotional tendencies and thematic patterns. We employ a multi-method approach integrating SnowNLP sentiment analysis based on Naive Bayes algorithm and Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA) topic modeling to identify emotional distributions and core discussion themes. Results reveal that positive sentiment dominates (58.1%), with five distinct topics identified: cultural connection, social media communication, brand preference, brand image, and consumption experience. Cross-analysis demonstrates significant sentiment-topic correlations, with collaborative marketing achieving the highest sentiment scores (0.78) while service experience topics exhibit substantial negative sentiment (20.9% negative proportion). These findings provide data-driven insights for optimizing emotional marketing strategies in competitive markets, demonstrating the practical value of integrating machine learning techniques for large-scale user feedback analysis. The methodology offers a systematic framework for brands to identify emotional value drivers and operational weaknesses, enabling targeted improvements in marketing effectiveness and service quality. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).},
